CPAP Therapy Oral Appliance Therapy Appointments Registration Packet Take the Tour Sleep Disorders Obstructive Sleep Apnea Children s Sleep Disorders Narcolepsy Restless Legs Syndrome Insomnia Sleep Resources Testimonials Referral Forms Physicians Dentists Contact Call Us Request Appointment CPAP Therapy Sleep Centers of Alaska Our Services CPAP Therapy Tweet Sleep Centers of Alaska Sleep Centers located in Anchorage, AK, Wasilla, AK & Soldotna, AK Positive airway pressure (PAP) therapy is the frontline treatment for obstructive sleep This form of therapy requires nightly use of a PAP device which is an electrical device, small enough to be placed on a nightstand, that connects to the patient via tubing and a For patients prescribed PAP therapy, Sleep Centers of Alaska, with locations in Anchorage, Wasilla, and provides the PAP device and related accessories and supplies such as masks, tubing, and With ongoing use of the PAP device, patients will periodically need replacement supplies for which Sleep Centers of Alaska offers a program through which patients may purchase these Request Appointment CPAP Therapy Q & A What is a CPAP device? If the PAP device delivers continuous pressurized air, it is referred to as a continuous positive airway pressure (CPAP) A CPAP device is an electrical device that provides pressurized air to the patient through tubing and a The machine, which is placed on a nightstand, has a pump that controls the airflow, a tube that carries the air from the machine to the patient, and a mask that goes over the patient’s mouth, nose, or The PAP device takes in air from the room, lightly pressurizes it, and then delivers to the patient through the mask a constant stream of pressurized The pressurized air serves to keep the airway passages open during sleep, thus eliminating snoring and the pauses in breathing that are caused by the sleep With use of the PAP device, breathing becomes regular, snoring stops, the patient is not awakened by lack of oxygen, and restful sleep is To determine the right level of air pressure necessary to alleviate the sleep apnea, a titration polysomnography is generally conducted as an overnight study in the sleep What types of masks are available? There are many types of masks used with the CPAP Some cover both the nose and mouth others cover only the Alternatively, "nasal pillows" fit into the No matter what type of mask is used, it is important that it fits well and makes a good seal to prevent air leaks and maintain the right level of pressurized It may take some time to find the right mask but the goal is to find the one that is not only comfortable but also Some CPAP machines also come with humidifiers to prevent your nose and throat from becoming dry while you breathe pressurized air during the What if the machine is uncomfortable? Staff members work with patients to find the type of mask that is the most Tension on the straps of the mask may need to be adjusted so that the mask fits securely and Also, the settings on the machine may need to be adjusted accordingly Request Appointment What we offer Services Consultations more info Sleep Studies more info CPAP Therapy more info Oral Appliance Therapy more info Privacy Policy Terms & Conditions Nondiscrimination Policy Contact Us Sleep Centers of Alaska, Anchorage, AK Phone (appointments): | Phone (general inquiries): Address: East Tudor Road, Suite , Anchorage , AK Sleep Centers of Alaska, Wasilla, AK Phone (appointments): | Phone (general inquiries): Address: West Parks Highway, Suite , Wasilla , AK Sleep Centers of Alaska, Soldotna, AK Phone (appointments): | Phone (general inquiries): (907) Address: Rockwell Avenue, Suite , Soldotna , AK Sleep Centers of Alaska, Anchorage , AK Phone (appointments): | Phone (general inquiries): Address: Laurel Street, Suite , Anchorage , AK ×   Are You Getting Enough Sleep? - Anchorage, AK & Wasilla, AK: Sleep Centers of Alaska More Home Services Consultations Sleep Studies Are You Getting Enough Sleep? iAccess Life is a mobile app that lets users with disabilities rate, review & research places based on their Download our app and find accessible places near you! iAccess Life will provide users with a wealth of knowledge around the accessibility of establishments such as restaurants, hotels, concert venues, and sporting arenas so they can easily find wheelchair accessible places and establishments that accommodate their The app will allow our users to “know before they go” and feel confident making plans with their friends, colleagues, and loved Now available in the iOS and Google Play app Features Category Selection Select your desired business, for example, “Restaurants.” These places will populate using the location services on the phone and the Google Places Location Profile The location profile contains necessary information such as address, phone number, and location On the location page, users can see an overall accessibility rating, the locations rating from Google places and the specific average ratings around parking, entrance, seating, and Map View The map view will be populated with most accessible establishments that are near your location or the establishments that meet your category search You can either click on the PIN of the place you want more information for to open the location profile or you will have the option to select the hamburger menu in the top right corner of the page to see a full list of locations so you can easily find accessible places near you! Ratings & Reviews On the location profile page, a user will be able to give a rating for the Entrance, Bathroom, Parking, and Interior seating of the In addition to the ranks, users will be able to write a text review, by clicking “Add a ” Users can rate, review & research places based on their accessibility and let others know where to find wheelchair accessible places and places that accommodate other List View The list view will be populated with most accessible establishments that are near your location or the establishments that meet your category search criteria in a You can click the location from the list view that you want more information for in order to open the location User Profile & Location Favorites Users will need to register with the app to leave ratings & Once a user creates a profile, they will be able to maintain their profile This profile information includes their specific disability so that they can receive tailored They will also be able to favorite locations that permeate to the top of their searches when applicable to the search Download iAccess Life Mission Preview As Featured On Partners Keep up with our progress! FDA granted Breakthrough Device Designation for Niyad™ FDA grants Breakthrough Designation to devices that have the potential for improved efficacy in the treatment of a Niyad™ provides an option for anticoagulation that does not exist today and is an improvement over the standard of care, especially in patients undergoing CRRT that cannot tolerate heparin or are at a higher risk of Breakthrough Designation has many benefits such as expedited review by But more importantly, it allows for CMS reimbursement of up to % of the cost over the existing The program is designed to encourage adoption of new technology immediately upon commercialization and should greatly enhance the value of both Niyad™ and and Dialysis When the kidneys are no longer working effectively, waste products and fluid in the Dialysis takes over a portion of the function of the failing kidneys to remove the fluid and Dialysis is typically needed when approximately percent of the patient’s kidney function is Kidney function can be lost rapidly (acute kidney injury) or over months or years (chronic kidney disease). Breastfeeding FAQ | MamaMend Weekly Digest Blog Breastfeeding Chat Log in Create account Breastfeeding Frequently Asked Questions + How do I get my baby to latch on properly? Here are some tips to help your baby’s latch: Tickle the baby’s lips to encourage him or her to open Pull your baby close so that the chin and lower jaw moves into your breast Watch the lower lip and aim it as far from base of nipple as possible, so the baby takes a large mouthful of + Which position is best for breastfeeding? Some moms find that the following positions are helpful ways to get comfortable and support their babies while You also can use pillows under your arms, elbows, neck, or back to give you added comfort and Keep trying different positions until you are What works for one feeding may not work for the next CLUTCH OR “FOOTBALL” HOLD: useful if you have had a , or if you have large breasts, flat or inverted nipples, or a strong This hold is also helpful for babies who like to be in a more upright position when they Hold your baby at your side with the baby lying on his or her back and with his or her head at the level of your Support your baby’s head by placing the palm of your hand at the base of his or her OR TRANSITIONAL HOLD: useful for premature babies or babies with a weak suck because this hold gives extra head support and may help the baby stay Hold your baby along the area opposite from the breast you are Support your baby’s head at the base of his or her neck with the palm of your CRADLE HOLD: an easy, common hold that is comfortable for most mothers and Hold your baby with his or her head on your forearm and his or her body facing HOLD (STRADDLE HOLD): a more relaxed, Lie back on a Lay your baby against your body with your baby’s head just above and between your Gravity and an instinct to nurse will guide your baby to your As your baby searches for your breast, support your baby’s head and shoulders but don’t force the POSITION: useful if you have had a , but also allows you to rest while the baby Lie on your side with your baby facing Pull your baby close so your baby faces your + How can I ease the pain of breastfeeding? Many moms say their breasts feel tender when they first start A mother and her baby need time to find comfortable breastfeeding positions and a good If breastfeeding hurts, your baby may be sucking on only the Gently break your baby’s suction to your breast by placing a clean finger in the corner of your baby’s Then try again to get your baby to latch To find out whether your baby is sucking only on your nipple, check what your nipple looks like when it comes out of your baby’s Your nipple should not look flat or It should look round and long or the same shape it was before the + How often should I feed my newborn? Early and often! Newborns usually need to nurse at least eight to times every This also helps make sure you will make plenty of Healthy babies develop their own feeding Follow your baby’s cues for when he or she is ready to + Can I breastfeed and bottle feed my baby at the same time? If your goal is to breastfeed, it is generally best to wait to introduce a bottle or pacifier until after breastfeeding is established (usually around weeks). + How long do you feed on each breast? There is no set time for They may be to minutes per They may be shorter or Your baby will let you know when he or she is finished If you worry that your baby is not getting enough milk, talk to your baby’s + How long should I breastfeed? Many leading health organizations recommend that most infants breastfeed for at least months, with exclusive breastfeeding for the first six This means that babies are not given any foods or liquids other than breastmilk for the first six + How long does the average mom breastfeed? Here are some current breastfeeding rates for the US: Ever % At 6 months % At 1 year % Exclusively through 3 months % Exclusively through 6 months % The average length of breastfeeding is weeks in the + How do I wean my breastfed baby? Weaning should be gradual, so your breasts don’t become painfully If your baby is still very young, you may need to express some milk from your breasts or pump a tiny amount if your breasts become Do not express or pump the amount you normally would for a When you pump or nurse, your breasts make more milk in By removing less milk than normal, your breasts will make less Contact an IBCLC if you have overly full breasts while You will need to substitute your milk with formula if your baby is younger than 1 If your baby is older than 1 year, you can stop offering the breast and drop one feeding a time, over several Start by taking away his or her least favorite feeding Nursing sessions that come before falling asleep or after waking are often the ones to go Wait a few days to drop another Avoid sitting in your special nursing chair, but do offer extra cuddles or babywearing during this transition so your child can still enjoy being close to Distract your child wit

TriAxia Health – Improving outcomes for rare disease patients by enabling the selection and discovery of the most effective treatments Skip to content TriAxia Health Improving outcomes for rare disease patients by enabling the selection and discovery of the most effective treatments Menu Scroll down to content About TriAxia Health Intelligent aggregation, enrichment and analysis of rare disease patient data for Providers, Biopharmas, and Payers OUR MISSION At TriAxia Health, our mission is to improve health outcomes for patients living with rare diseases by enabling the selection and discovery of the most effective treatments for each We do so through collaboration across leading provider networks, the integration of clinical and molecular patient information, and a unique data partnership to access proprietary health claims and prescriptions history covering % of the US Collaboration: Since the number of patients at any given medical center, even one specializing in rare disease, is too small to develop a complete understanding of the disease (exacerbated by the tendency of rare diseases to have high hazard ratios), the TAH platform is used by multiple leading hospital systems , each of whom provides both quaternary and community care, so that the aggregation of their collective patient data (from their EMRs)provides the necessary combination of depth (number of patients) and breadth (variety of treatment approaches) necessary to understand their Clinical & molecular patient information: Since % of rare diseases have a genetic etiology , fully understanding these diseases to provide both the best treatments today and enable the search for new cures in the future requires the combination of clinical and molecular (genomic, proteomic, metabolomic) data . Supported by Illumina , TAH is combining molecular data tailored to a given rare disease with clinical data to provide a unique, understanding of each Data partnership: The average rare disease patient takes years to receive an accurate diagnosis, and aggregating patients across care settings results in an ‘open panel’ for We address both issues, while providing additional value to our provider clients, through a unique data partnership providing us with years of proprietary prescriptions and health claims history on % of the US We are building a , rare disease patient management platform to store, analyze and capitalize on novel insights for payers, providers and life science companies who collaborate to help people with these diseases receive the best We hope you’ll join A new home builder has a lot at stake with… Read more Posts navigation 1 2 Next 11 Modern Lending, LLC | NMLS#1738930 | AZBR#0947744 | N Drinkwater Blvd #300 Scottsdale, AZ | NMLS Consumer Access   Frequently Asked Mortgage Questions | Modern Home Lending Apply Learn Blog FAQ Mortgage Calculator About Evan Einhorn Troy Fjerkenstad Contact Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) The basics of a mortgage How do I qualify for a mortgage? Qualifying is the first step to purchasing a We can guide you through the simple application process over the phone, online , or in We’ll look at many different qualification factors and will need some dcoumentation to complete the qualification Qualification criteria vary by different loan One borrower may qualify for one mortgage loan option and not However, there are typically three things that you usually need… Income Employment History – Most loan programs require an income and employment However, there are some programs that allow borrowers who recently started jobs or might have strong assets to Keep in mind, we can usually take into account multiple different types of income (job, rental income, child support, retirement, pension, alimony, disability, etc). Credit – Most loan programs need some kind of credit Although there are some unique programs that allow low or no credit scores to Down Payment or Equity – Different loan programs have different down payment requirements if you’re If refinancing, there will be some requirement for equity as With this being said, there are down payment assistance options that will cover most or all of buyer’s down What s included in my mortgage payment? Many use the abbreviation of PITI to explain the different components of a mortgage With many mortgages, there are options for homeowners to pay their taxes and or insurance separate if they However, most homebuyers include it in their monthly payment to help keep month of even housing Principal – portion of your mortgage payment that goes to paying down your loan Interest – monthly interest that you pay to your mortgage lender for your loan Taxes – property tax bill that you pay yourself or through your escrow account Insurance – your homeowner’s insurnace (also known as hazard insurance) Two other monthly obligations that we consider when qualifying buyers and homeowners are mortgage insurance (sometimes required with lower down payment options) and HOA (community fees). How much do I need for a down payment? Down payment requirements vary from loan program to loan Below are the minimum down payment requirements for each loan – keep in mind that not everyone can qualify at the minimum down We help analyze all loan options and assist in determining the ideal down payment and Also keep in mind that there may be down payment assistance available to cover some or all of your down Loan Program Minimum Down Payment Conventional % FHA % Jumbo 5% VA 0% USDA Rural 0% Down Payment Assistance Available on Conventional, FHA, and VA loans How are mortgage rates determined? For the most part, rates move with financial markets (specifically, the bond market) as well as the Every client receives a custom rate specific to their specific scenario Did you also know that mortgage rates change daily? Even hourly? Rat

Jobs — StreetCred Home Team Jobs Blog Home Team Jobs Blog Jobs About StreetCred StreetCred is an startup focused on accessible This important mapping data is currently too restrictive, expensive, and low quality we want to change this Founded by mapping industry veterans with experience in creating developer networks, StreetCred believes in the power of software and data to solve difficult business We are excited about the decentralizing aspects of blockchain technology and are creating a protocol to encourage user compensation for data creation that provides , , accessible mapping data to companies and developers that need If we succeed, our work will live on We do our best work when we’re able to collaborate with great people who offer diverse perspectives on longstanding To that end, we’re looking for two or three great Given our early stage, it s important that the whole team has a high level of energy and Strong communication skills are important for any company, but critical for a team of this There are many questions to answer, ideas to share, decisions to debate, and processes to set If you’re someone that thrives in this type of environment we hope you’ll consider reaching out and getting to know We can’t wait to meet you! Software Engineer Choose Your Own Adventure! Since we re still new, there are many opportunities to shape your destiny as an early team We d like to share our rough descriptions of what we re working on and current technology We hope that something on our TODO list peaks your interest and sparks some ideas in your mind that you d be excited to share with Let s explore these solutions together and see where it This is not a checklist of requirements and we encourage you to apply if any one area sounds exciting to Geospatial Data Analysis An early focus will be to analyze existing geospatial data and to build predictive models around global points of We d love to chat about graph theory, data science, and machine learning applications in the geospatial Our goal is to understand what quality and coverage means and how it can be quantified for maximum insight into the data we ll collect on the StreetCred Interactive Web Portal To show off our data analysis, we re building an interactive web portal with dynamic maps and many opportunities to flex some data visualization If you ve got a knack for building beautiful rich dashboard experiences we ve gotta talk! Mobile Apps & SDKs We re building a reference app (likely in React Native) to show new users how to contribute Think Foursquare + Pokemon GO + There will be fun challenges like working with geolocation services and building SDKs to encourage other developers to join in on the fun of building apps on the StreetCred The app will require a reliable, scalable, backend that will take advantage of the latest and greatest in continuous integration, caching, pub sub frameworks, and of course data storage retrieval search. Blockchain Smart Contracts Token design StreetCred will incentivize users to create data using incentives, and decentralize this critical dataset using blockchain We re excited to talk to you about your experience, either professional or dabbling, with and all the various existing blockchain If you love reading whitepapers as much as we do, let s compare notes! Decentralized Data The StreetCred protocol is unique in that it aims to provide utility by accumulating data from all the various transactions on the network into a powerful and highly desirable data We re working toward an innovative data storage model that will optimize for decentralization, stability, and security in an pool of server nodes spread out across the If you love to geek out about torrents, sharding, and replication, please get in touch! Community Building We ll build the StreetCred protocol in an open, public way that encourages others to To this end, everyone on the team is focused on We welcome candidates who enjoy building usable technology that s accessible to others, and who are interested in speaking and writing about Ideally located in New York City but we will consider Benefits We’re building an open, positive, and inclusive culture that allows the team to enjoy their work and feel connected to their colleagues in meaningful Flexible work hours, , and fun team events allows each teammate to calibrate for individually optimal work life Our compensation packages are competitive and offer meaningful equity for our early We’ve also got you covered with important benefits, such as mandatory PTO, healthcare, , parental leave, and Please ask about anything particularly important to you and we can provide more Our office offers many benefits, such as free yoga meditation bootcamp classes, for There’s a place to park your bike and a great trail along the water to We’ve also got healthy snacks and beverages if thirst or hunger should We aim to provide many opportunities for each team member to publicly build their own brand through highly visible con

contact RNA interference offers a powerful means of silencing Our science & focus Our proprietary branched siRNA construct opens new frontiers in treating neurodegenerative diseases RNA interference is a Nobel discovery that allows for targeted silencing of A central limitation in using RNA interference (RNAi) to treat neurological diseases has been the difficulty of achieving distribution throughout the central nervous Many of the most pressing medical challenges in neurodegeneration require RNAi technologies to thoroughly reach all affected brain Our proprietary branched siRNA for the first time enables RNA interference to be deployed as a therapeutic approach throughout the brain and spinal RNA interference -- RNA interference: A natural mechanism to regulate genes Within human cells, genes are constantly being expressed by way of RNA is the message that conveys genetic directions into action in the RNA interference is a natural process that cells evolved to modulate gene This same process can be leveraged for therapeutics in the following 1 Short pieces of synthetic RNA are designed to target the message of the These are called small interfering RNA, or siRNA 2 These pieces of RNA join with the Argonaute proteins to form the enzymatic structure called the silencing complex, or RISC 3 One strand of the siRNA is discarded, and the RISC is activated for searching 4 The RISC scans for any and all matches within the cell’s gene messages 5 When it finds a match, the RISC destroys it, preventing the gene’s message from being translated into a functional protein, thus effectively modulating gene expression 6 The RISC is then free to search again Our proprietary RNAi platform: branched siRNA We have developed a novel oligonucleotide structure called branched siRNA, which for the first time can perform RNA interference throughout the brain and spinal Branched siRNA is a type of “informational ” Informational drugs share a common scaffold that supports their delivery and distribution, combined with a variable nucleic acid sequence that defines the drug’s The common scaffold for our therapeutics enables effective delivery to the central nervous system and a predictable safety This scaffold can be customized to target different genetic Scientific research is rapidly expanding our understanding of genetic contributors to neurodegenerative The programmable nature of branched siRNA allows for rapid generation of new therapeutic candidates based on the latest Branched siRNA provides unparalleled durability and distribution in the CNS Our

Every RIA firm needs rock solid One or more individuals must be dedicated to doing the job Many RIA firms can achieve better compliance results through outsourcing for three primary reasons: Effectiveness - Compliance officers can perform at their peak surrounded and supported by others in their Compliance professionals thrive in a setting that fosters knowledge sharing, collegial support and advancement Working as a cohesive unit we develop and share best practices, and apply them across our entire client Perspective - Many CCOs find it challenging to stay ahead of regulatory developments while working They lack the perspective enjoyed by members of a team serving multiple Our clients benefit from the reality that the new regulation vexing one firm today will likely impact the others before Cost - A cyclical compliance calendar makes efficient staffing nearly A dedicated CCO must be prepared for a heavy workload during critical periods, but at other times may be an underutilized cost And when the workload is most intense – , during a regulatory examination – it is difficult to ramp up capacity For the reasons described above, clients of Key Bridge recognize our ability to raise the quality of their compliance program while reducing total costs - freeing them to focus on serving their clients and growing their OUR TEAM CHERYL LEIBOWITZ ALISHA DOWELL DIRECTORS OUR ADDRESS WASHINGTON, DC K Street NW, Suite , Washington, DC Email: Phone: CINCINNATI, OH Innovation Alley, Suite G, Covington, KY Click Here to Find Us For any general inquiries, please fill in the following contact form: Thanks for submitting!
